<h2>HVAC Systems for San Diego</h2>
<p>San Diego's Mediterranean climate requires HVAC systems optimized for cooling efficiency rather than heating capacity. The ideal system for most San Diego homes is a high-efficiency air conditioning unit with a SEER rating of 16-20, paired with a heat pump or minimal heating system for the occasional cool days. Given that temperatures rarely drop below 40¬∞F or exceed 85¬∞F near the coast, homeowners can prioritize cooling performance and energy efficiency over heating capacity.</p>

